[Black "Bogoindian Defense #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6
{ An advantage of the move order  1...d5  2.c4  e6  3.Nf3  is that we can transpose to the Catalan unless the opponent plays the typical queen pawn variations 3...c5, 3....dxc4, 3....c6 3.....a6.  After I finished the course, I began to choose 3. Nf3 against certain opponents. }
2. c4
{ The move order  2.Nf3  e6  3.g3  d5  4.Bg2  allows us to avoid certain Catalan variations with 4. ... dxc4 and also the annoying 4. ... Bb4+. However, we allow 3 ... b5 and 4 ... b5, that lead to very different positions, but very interesting and useful to know, as these setups can be played with both colors.   Another problem of this move order is that Black is not forced to play 2. ... e6 and, usually plays 2. ... d5 immediately, keeping the option of developing the bishop on c8 outside the pawn chain or playing a quick c5 before e6.   I would recommend this move order if you play against someone with a very fixed repertoire and who always wants to vary within the Catalan. This way, you can limit the scope of the preparation a lot. }
2... e6 3. Nf3 Bb4+
{ 3...Bd2  seems playable to me as well, but I think this move leads to positions with more play and, above all, that Black's mistakes give us more advantage on average. Having the bishop pair available in most variations is always a not inconsiderable plus. }
4. Nbd2 O-O 5. a3 Be7
{ This retreat tries to punish the delicate position of the knight on d2 in exchange of giving up the center. }
6. e4 d5
{ Black tries to take advantage of the fact that the knight on d2 disturbs the development of White's pieces, but White's development is very dangerous. }
7. e5 Nfd7 8. Bd3 c5 9. h4
{ We threaten a typical attacking maneuver against the castling and force Black to weaken. Here we can see perfectly the benefit for Black of making the prophylactic move 4...a5!? }
9... h6 10. Bb1 cxd4 11. cxd5 exd5 12. Qc2 f5 13. Nb3 Nc6 14. Bf4
{ Black's structure is deplorable and, once we win the d4-pawn back, we will have a great long-term advantage. }
