{ This idea has already been seen on a couple of occasions in Grandmaster games and I find the approach very interesting as it has several small pitfalls. }
9. Qxc4 b5
{ Black exploits the fact that  10.axb5  would create drama in White's troops after  10...axb5! }
10. Qd3
{ It seems Black will have problems as White is threatening both b5 and Ne5, dominating the diagonal. }
10... Bb7 11. axb5 Be4 12. Qb3 Bd5
{ The queen cannot keep on defending the b5-pawn and, in case of going for another queen move, after recapturing on b5, Black would have an improved version of the Catalan. }
