{ We delay the capture on c4 in order to generate future threats with d5. }
9... Nc6 10. Qxc4 b5 11. Qb3 bxa4 12. Qxa4 Nb4 13. Qb3
{ We have a very clear plan, taking advantage of the weakness on c7. First, we trade off the dark squared bishops and then put pressure on c5. It is possible that an eventual maneuver Ne1-Nd3 could be deadly. }
