Rfe1
{ Here we can appreciate fully the usefulness of delaying Rfd1 when we can. }
12... Bd5
{ Black can also try to give up the light squared bishop to close the pawn structure and claim some degree of solidness has been achieved.   First, starting with  12...Bd5  would annoy a bit our Queen and taking on d5 would be awful as we intend to play e2-e4. The thing is, we still have a pair of bishops, so black is in trouble. }
13. Qd3 Bxf3 14. Qxf3 c6 15. e4 e5 16. Rad1
{ I do not see a satisfactory answer to the plan of playing f4-e5 after Kh1 and Qe2. }
