12. Qc3 c5 { The main option. } 13. Be3 Ne4
{ 13...cxd4  14.Qxd4  The more minor pieces, the better. Trading queens now would give us a very good winning chances. }
14. Qe1 Nb4 15. Rxa8 Qxa8 16. Nc3 Nxc3 17. bxc3 Nc2 18. Qc1 Nxe3 19. Qxe3
{ Playing a position like this is always a good option because Black will have to defend for the rest of the game while White isn't running any risk.  Black does have some compensation here, but the extra pawn is giving us a stable and lasting advantage. }
