8. dxc5 Qc7 9. Nxc4 Rd8 10. Qa4
{ It seems to me a very creative idea to make way to the rooks on the c and d-files. }
10... Qxc5 11. Nc3 Nd5 12. Rd1
{ Since Black cannot capture on c3 because of the back rank mate, the pressure on d5 is very strong, and it does not promise a very comfortable future for Black when we continue developing the bishop on c1 and the rook to a1. }
