14. Qc2 Bf5 15. Qd2 Bh3 16. Re1 Rad8 17. Qc3
{ After Be3 and Nd2 we finish our development. Black should continue playing with great creativity and dynamism, while we have some security since, in general, we have few and quite obvious moves at the defensive level. It seems to me a viable option since Black has, as we had mentioned, the unfinished business of the pawns on c7 and a7 that can cause problems in the long term. }
17... Qd5 { This move forces us to change a bit our plan. } 18. f3 Rfe8 19. Na3
{ We neutralize the attack and continue with the development comfortably with the considerations mentioned above. }
