7... Qd6 8. O-O Qa6 9. Qc2
{ A less explored move that allows us to keep avoiding forced lines. } 9... Nc6
{ 9...Rd8  10.Rd1  followed by Ne4, which will allow us to resume the pressure on c4. }
10. Nxc6 bxc6 11. Bg5 h6 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. e3 e5 14. d5
{ The engine is happy and goes straight into this position, but to me, it seems very difficult to play with Black. We will regain one of the pawns on the c-file, and Black should play very precise if he wants to equalize. In contrast, we will have a strong bishop on g2 and a very healthy pawn structure. }
