5. Bg2 O-O
{ The evolution of chess theory does not follow the same guidelines as it did 20 years ago. The playing strength of today's engines gives us answers understandable to a human  (not based exclusively on brute force and calculation)  and with a high degree of reliability in a matter of minutes.   Therefore, I consider it necessary to give a few alternatives to the main line  6.O-O  . They have a very low cost of time and allow us to avoid many variants that at a particular level can bother us, since it is feasible not to remember everything or prefer to dodge a little the main options.   A personal recommendation for the management of this course would be to start with some of these less ambitious but playable variations than 6.O-O, and as we progressively absorb the knowledge of the main lines, we can dare with 6.O-O.    Realistically, at this point in the opening we should already know very well Black's alternatives with 4.... dxc4. }
6. Nc3
{ With this move, we intend to pre-empt 6... dxc4 and avoid most of the critical lines. }
6... dxc4 { 6...c6  7.O-O  transpose to chapter 7. } 7. Ne5
{ We are in the same variation with 7. Ne5, but the difference is that there is a knight on c3 and we have not castled. I think this benefits us slightly. }
7... Qd6 8. O-O Rd8 9. Nb5 Qb6 10. a4
{ We defend d4, and we want to take on c4, winning a tempo. } 10... c6 11. Nxc4
Qa6 12. Nba3
{ 12.Nc7  was not possible as after  12...Qxc4  Black has a good position, and it will be very difficult for our knight to get out of a8. }
12... Bxa3 13. Nxa3 e5 14. b4
{ We accept that we lose a pawn but, in return, we open lines for our bishops. }
14... exd4
{ 14...Rxd4  15.Qe1  We have a very nice compensation for the pawn. We have the bishop pair, better development, Black has difficulties to defend e5 and the expansion with b5 will always be annoying for Black. }
15. Bf4
{ Black's knight on b8 will be difficult to develop as d4 will be left undefended. Ideas like e4, taking advantage of the pin, and a5, isolating the queen on a6, could be our next moves. }
