12... Qxc5 13. Be3 Qc7
{ 13...Qh5  14.f3  In this case we could also consider to castle long. } 14. f3
{ We have the typical position with an advantage for us. The pawn on c4 is weak and combines very badly with the Black's light-squared bishop. The pawns on e2-f3 do well controlling the light squares; e.g. moves like h3 and perhaps g4 would be possible in the future.   Our bishop can go on d4, and we can try to find a presence on the d-file. Between the weak c4-pawn and the a7-pawn, Black will always have a slightly worse and uncomfortable position. }
