{ I really like the flexibility that this move gives us, even though it has been played in one out of a hundred games in this position. The knight can go to c3 or d2, we defend c4 and support a future e4. We also keep b3 in reserve if necessary. }
7... b6 8. b3 a5
{ Because of this move, I prefer 8.b3 to @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/p2nbppp/1pp1pn2/3p4/2PP4/3Q1NP1/PP2PPBP/RNB2RK1 w kq - 0 8@@EndFEN@@  8.Nc3  . In this way, we can play the knight for d2. }
