8. b3 b6 9. Nc3 Bb7 10. Rd1
{ We will wait for Black to weaken his center with c5 before we take on d5. If Black doesn't play this move, we can continue our development with moves like Bb2 and Rac1. Later, some Ne5 ideas would gain a lot of strength. }
10... c5 11. cxd5 exd5 12. Qf5
{ White is always to be preferred in these kinds of positions with the pawns on c5 and d5, where we're able to put pressure on many areas of the board. After Bb2 and Rac1 Black has to watch out for moves like Nh4 followed by Nf5, Ne5, putting pressure in the center, or Bh3, which will attack c8, which is an important square for Black's rooks. }
