Bb2 19. a3 { As we can see, all the variation is very concrete. } 19... Bxa1
20. axb4 axb4 21. g4
{ I recommend playing this novelty. We want to gain space on the kingside. The g4-pawn cannot be taken, as we would win Black's important central pawn on d5. }
21... Bxg4 22. Bxd5 Nxd5 23. Qxd5 Rc8 24. Nd2 Bh3 25. f4
{ The queen is in a dominant position and with pawns on the e and f-files we always have chances of creating a passed pawn. }
