Bf4 g5
{ Black must first deflect the bishop from the pressure it is putting on c7. }
11. Be3 f5 12. Qc1 h6
{ If g4,  Ne1-d3 followed by f3 would be the ideal thing to do against the Stonewall. }
13. h4
{ We take advantage of the fact that Black still has a very exposed kingside. If Black takes on h4 we will recapture with the pawn and, suddenly, the attack after Kh1-Rg1 is not negligible. In addition, we threaten hxg5, and he will have to take with the knight, otherwise he will lose the pawn. As Black will not be able to keep the pawn structure, White has a clear advantage. }
13... gxh4 14. gxh4 { Now we can use the open g-file. } *

