2. c4
{ The move order  2.Nf3  e6  3.g3  d5  4.Bg2  allows us to avoid certain Catalan variations with 4. ... dxc4 and also the annoying 4. ... Bb4+. However, we allow 3 ... b5 and 4 ... b5, that lead to very different positions, but very interesting and useful to know, as these setups can be played with both colors.   Another problem of this move order is that Black is not forced to play 2. ... e6 and, usually plays 2. ... d5 immediately, keeping the option of developing the bishop on c8 outside the pawn chain or playing a quick c5 before e6.   I would recommend this move order if you play against someone with a very fixed repertoire and who always wants to vary within the Catalan. This way, you can limit the scope of the preparation a lot. }
2... e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Bb4+ 5. Bd2 Bd6
{ This retreat became fashionable 5–6 years ago, One of the main reasons is the fact that White's intuitive plan Bg5-Bf6-Nbd2-Qc2-e4 gives good play for Black.   5...Bxd2+  6.Nbxd2  It will be difficult for Black to have presence in the center. Usually, our bishop on d2 is annoying, but it is not the case.   A plan that I really like after Black plays b6 would be Rc1-Qc2 and taking on d5. When Black recaptures with the pawn, we can relocate our knight on c3, and then it will be an improved version of the extensively spoken Queen's Indian structure.   The weaknesses on the dark squares will allow White to generate pressure with a3-b4 and Ne5-f4 ideas. }
6. Bg2 O-O 7. O-O dxc4
{ Black wants to justify the move Bd6 by gaining space in the center with e5. Subsequently, he would want to play c6 and neutralize our bishop on g2. }
8. Qc2 Nc6 9. Rd1
{ So far, we are stopping  9...e5  as we take two times, and then we play Bb4. }
9... Qe7 10. Na3
{ Against Qe7, unlike with Re8, the pawn on  d4  is not left undefended after  10...Bxa3  . }
10... Bxa3 11. bxa3 Qxa3 12. Qxc4
{ In exchange for a pawn, we have the bishop pair and two files to put pressure on b7 and c7. A plan that I like a lot in this position is Ne1-Nd3 to jump to c5.   Black will suffer a lot with the lack of flexibility of his queenside pawn structure. }
