9... Re8 10. a4 e5 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Nxe5 Bxe5 13. Na3
{ Our knight on c4 will effectively annoy the bishop on e5. Apart from looking for options for our bishop on d2 and taking advantage of the d-file, our priority will be to control the activity of the bishop on c8, which is Black's most uncomfortable problem. }
13... c3 14. Bxc3 Qe7 15. Bxe5 Qxe5 16. e4
{ The knight on f6 and the bishop on c8 against our pawn structure, and we will gain full control of the open file and the center after Rd3-Rad1 and Nc4. }
