8... cxd4 9. Nxc6 bxc6 10. Qxd4 Qb6 { The only move that annoys our plans. }
11. Qg4 { We continue harassing g7, and we want again to take on c4. } 11... h5
12. Qxc4 { Once Black's castling is weakened, we can calmly capture on c4. }
12... Bxa3 13. bxa3 O-O 14. Qc2
{ A useful rule of thumb: we usually need two weaknesses to win a game, as our opponent will hardly be able to defend both. c6 and h5 are our candidates and the pair of bishops guarantees us a long-term advantage, being the position so open. }
