21. Be4
{ We block on d3, and we will follow with b5 to put pressure on b7. Black's central majority will struggle to expand, given his reduced control on the light squares.   Being a pawn down is really anecdotal, Black's bishop is incognito and Black's weak castling will always guarantee us counterplay. }
