13. Nxd7 Qxd7 14. Ne5 Qe7
{ Special mention to the fact that I find it very unnatural to play this way with Black. }
15. Bxd5 exd5 16. Qxd5 Bb6 { We cannot take on c6 as e2 is in the air. } 17.
Qd7 Qxd7 18. Nxd7 Rfe8 19. Nxb6 axb6 20. e3
{ Bishop vs knight with pawns on both sides and the queenside weaknesses result in a very uncomfortable endgame to defend. Based on all the subtleties that Black has had to do, we will make him suffer for a longer period of time. }
