9. Naxc4 Rc8 10. Qb3 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 Bc6 12. Bxc6+
{ It has been played in only 3 games of the more than 50 in this position. Our knight on e5 gives us more than the Catalan bishop. }
12... bxc6 13. Rd1 Qc7
{ 13...c5  14.e3  The check on the a4-square followed by opening the d-file will be decisive.   13...Be7  14.Qa4  We will take the pawn on d4, and we will have a very typical advantage in the Catalan. We will put pressure on the isolated pawn on the c-file, and Black has no counterplay.   In addition, the rooks have access to the queenside along the 3rd rank. In fact, Black has two isolated pawns 2 on the c and a-files c and our pawn structure is practically flawless, so we have a maximum flexibility. }
14. Nc4 c5 15. Bf4 Qc6 16. Rac1 Be7
{ It seems that the worst is over for Black and that he will be able to castle quietly. }
17. Rxd4
{ That is why tactics are important! It has to be combined with strategic ideas and create the perfect storm against our opponent. }
17... cxd4 18. Nd6+ Bxd6 19. Rxc6 Rxc6 20. Qb7
{ And Black will lose either the rook on c8 or the one on a8. } *

