8... Nd7 9. Nxc4 b5
{ 9...Nxe3  10.Nxe3  Be7  11.d5  We increase our power on the light squares; the bishop on g2 is very strong and the simple fact of moving the queen away to put a rook on d1 will pose more problems to Black than what it may seem at first sight. Later, in the model games chapter, we will see how I won this game. }
10. dxc5 { An important nuance that I had to calculate in my game. } 10... bxc4
{ 10...Nxc5  11.b4!  We want to displace the knight on c5  11...Na4  12.Bd4  Not being able to develop the bishop on el f8 is a very serious problem for Black's king safety. The knight on d5 will be our target for harassment once we have finished the development of the rest of our pieces. }
11. Bxd5 exd5 12. Qxd5 Rb8 13. c6
{ Regaining the piece, and the extra pawn, together with our development advantage, proves to be decisive. }
