{ 11...O-O  12.e3  Tenemos We reached the ideal kind of position when being a pawn down. }
12. Qe4 O-O { We cannot play  13.Rd1  due to  13...Nf3+  Be careful! } 13. Ba3
{ Now we threaten Rd1 and at the same time we attack the poor rook on f8, which has just come into play. }
13... f5 14. Qb1
{ And the double threat on b7 and f8 is decisive, together of the problems that Black has because of his lack of development.   14...Nxe2+  15.Kh1  Nc3  else, we trap the e2-knight  16.Qb3  Nd5  17.Bxf8  one way or the other we will retrieve one pawn if not two, and with open lines in the center our extra rook will do more damage than Black's undeveloped minor pieces. }
