9. Be3 Qxb2 10. O-O Nd5
{ 10...Qxa1?  11.Nc3  Qb2  12.Rb1  Qa3  13.Bxb7  White is winning. } 11. Bxd5
exd5 12. Qxd5 Be6 13. Qe4 Qxa1 14. Qxb7 Qxa2 15. Qxa8 Bd6 16. Nc3 Qa6 17. Nd3
{ After a lot of only moves by Black and being a tightrope, we reach a position where Black will lose the pawn on a7 and will have to suffer a 4 against 3 pawn majority but with knights in our favor that play better on one side of the board. }
