{ Black wants to play b5 and consolidate his extra pawn on c4. This line is mainly known as being an interesting way to unbalance. Both  6.O-O  and  6.a4  would be the main alternatives. However, for this course, we reply in an analogous way to 5. ... a6.   I consider that it is easier to remember a repetition if we more or less play similar plans each time. In the case of this course, Ne5 should be the most popular move. }
