10. a4 f6 11. Ng4
{ With this move we intend to play e4 and bring the knight on e3 to enhance a future d5. }
11... a5 12. axb5 cxb5
{ 12...Bxc3  13.bxc3  cxb5  14.e4  followed by Ba3, White have a dream position, only one pawn down to trade fast piece development, powerful bishop pair, center control. }
13. Nxb5 Nc6 14. Ne3 Ba6 15. Qe4
{ And after:  15...Bxb5  16.Qxe6  we recover the piece on d5, and we are left with a pawn advantage, and if  16...Kh8  we capture with bishop to put pressure on c6  17.Bxd5  . }
