2... e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 Bb4+ 6. Bd2 a5
{ In this similar variation to the Bogo-Indian, Black defends the bishop and gains space on the queenside. In case the bishop is captured, this would also activate the rook.    A significant difference of the variation is that it facilitates the move b5, defending the recently captured pawn on c4, since the rook will not be so vulnerable to the bishop on g2. }
