{ We deviate from the main lines. We want to take on c4 and take advantage of the fact that Black has a lot of minor pieces in the center.   8.Qb5  , Narayanan's recommendation in his Catalan course, I find it playable too, so I prefer to give you an alternative. }
8... b5 9. a4 Bxd2+
{ As the move a6 is not an option, Black takes advantage of a couple of forced  moves to enable c6 and keep his pawn structure. }
10. Nbxd2 Ncb4 11. Qc1 c6 12. O-O O-O 13. b3 c3
{ 13...cxb3  14.Nxb3  a5  15.Qb2  We have already seen this type of pawn structures and here the weakness on a5 is more notorious. We will make good use of the c5 square and Black will not be able to get rid of his weak queenside pawns if he does not play precise. }
14. Ne4 bxa4 15. Rxa4 c2 16. Qd2
{ We get the c2-pawn back after Rc1-Ne1-Nxc2 and Black will struggle due to having two weaknesses on a7 and c6 apart from us having the c5-square for the knight. It should be noted that in this case we will not be a pawn down, as usual in these structures. }
