[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6
{ An advantage of the move order  1...d5  2.c4  e6  3.Nf3  is that we can transpose to the Catalan unless the opponent plays the typical queen pawn variations 3...c5, 3....dxc4, 3....c6 3.....a6.  After I finished the course, I began to choose 3. Nf3 against certain opponents. }
2. c4
{ The move order  2.Nf3  e6  3.g3  d5  4.Bg2  allows us to avoid certain Catalan variations with 4. ... dxc4 and also the annoying 4. ... Bb4+. However, we allow 3 ... b5 and 4 ... b5, that lead to very different positions, but very interesting and useful to know, as these setups can be played with both colors.   Another problem of this move order is that Black is not forced to play 2. ... e6 and, usually plays 2. ... d5 immediately, keeping the option of developing the bishop on c8 outside the pawn chain or playing a quick c5 before e6.   I would recommend this move order if you play against someone with a very fixed repertoire and who always wants to vary within the Catalan. This way, you can limit the scope of the preparation a lot. }
2... e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 Nc6 6. Qa4 Bb4+ 7. Bd2 Bd6 8. Na3 Ne4
{ I came across this variant in World Blitz and the response on the board didn't seem so trivial to me. }
9. Nxc4 Nxd2 10. Nfxd2
{ In the game I captured c's knight and there is no very clear way to embarrass Black, so he can't play e6-e5. }
10... Bd7 11. e3 O-O 12. Qb3
{ We have an ideal pawn structure and having exchanged the dark-squared bishop favors us since Black does not have a comfortable way to open the position.   In case of  12...e5  we will continue with  13.d5  and Ne4 and Black will be in serious trouble. }
12... b5
{ This has been followed in correspondence, but for humans it would be somewhat scary to allow  13.Nxd6  cxd6  and  14.d5  destroying the black structure. The point is that black dynamically holds up, but it seems very difficult for someone to want to get into it. }
13. Nxd6 cxd6 14. O-O
{ We could go on with Qa3 and look for annoyance at the d6 point and at Black's exposed queenside. We have an extremely comfortable position, and it will be our task to make sense of the d2-knight in due course. }
