Be4
{ Black takes advantage of the pin to strengthen the e4-square and prevent our eventual central expansion. }
8. Qa4 Nc6 { The threats are Bxd2 and Nxd4. } 9. O-O Bxd2 10. Bxd2 Bxf3 11.
exf3
{ The key! Black's lack in development allows us to go for this option.   11.Bxf3  would allow  11...Nxd4  12.Bxa8  Nxe2+  and after taking on a8, Black's two extra pawns for the exchange even the scales. }
11... Nxd4 12. Rfe1 O-O 13. f4 c5 14. Bc3
{ Taking the rook on a8 now would be counterproductive. After Qxa8, we would have no satisfactory reply against Nf3+. }
14... Rc8 15. Rad1
{ We will get the pawn back, and we will have a comfortable position with a strong bishop and a pawn on d7 that will be a target. }
