15... Nd7 16. gxf5 Nf6 { We never have to underestimate development. } 17. Ne2
{ We want to head for g3 or maybe also have the option of Bh3-Kh1-Rg1.   17.Rc1  also looks natural with the subsequent maneuver Qb3-c2. }
17... Nh5 18. Qb3+ { We seek to enter e6 and force Black into a move. } 18...
Bd5 19. Qc2
{ We threaten the e4-pawn and also Nc3 as well. The benefit of having forced the extra move, Bd5, is very clear. }
