8. e4 d4
{ Black wants to keep his three central pawns. Otherwise, the  compensation will be gradually reduced with each pawn exchange. }
9. Nb1 { Our goal is building a blockade on light squares. } 9... Bb7 10. Bd3
Bxe4 11. Bxe4 Nxe4 12. O-O
{ The next moves are very easy to play. We have to put pressure on e6, and Black wants to defend and develop at the same time. }
12... Ndf6 13. Nbd2 Nxd2 14. Bxd2 Qd5 15. Re1 Bd6 16. Qe2 Kd7 17. Rac1
{ After Qd3 we can continue with moves like Bg5-Nd2, we have absolute control of the light squares. Black's king will always be exposed and, once we have controlled Black's center, he can do little. }
