{ Another novelty. Here as well we can apply what I mentioned, including a6-a4 or not. }
10... Na6 11. Bxa6 bxa6 12. Qd2
{ With the pawn on e4, this position clearly favors White, as Black will not be able to play f5 due to e5 and should stay passive. }
