10. a4 Qe7
{ Defending d6 and, therefore, making possible for the knight to develop to d7. }
11. Be2 Nbd7 12. O-O Ne8
{ Black activates his strong bishop on g7 and prepares his expansion on the queenside. }
13. a5
{ A typical move that prevents Black from keeping the pawn island d-c-b. }
13... Rb8
{ 13...Ne5  14.Nd2  f5  15.Qb3  Once the knight is on b6 we can start mobilizing our center with moves like Rf1-Bg3-f4-e4. Black can do little more than observing, White's domination is total. }
14. Nd2 b5 15. axb6 Rxb6
{ 15...Nxb6  16.Nb3  Black cannot prevent White to enter via a5 while defending c5 at the same time. }
16. Nc4 Rb4 17. Na5 { The infiltration on c6 is decisive. } *

