10. Rd1 Qb6 { Black intends to create an immediate counterplay against b2. }
11. Ng5 { 11.Rxd5  Bxb2  12.Be3  Qa6  13.Ng5  h5  14.Bf3  . } 11... Nf6 12. Nc3
{ Nd5 is on the menu and Black has not a lot of good options. } 12... h6 13.
Nge4 h5
{ 13...Nxe4  14.Bxe4  and both Nd5 ideas and the fact that the h6-pawn is threatened give Black troubles. }
14. Rb1
{ Defending b2 and we will follow with Be3 and Rbc1. White's position is quite armonious. }
