Rb5 Qa3
{ If  20...Qa6  we can continue attacking with  21.Bf1  . We have more than compensation for the pawn thanks to Black's piece awkwardness. We have more than enough compensation for the pawn due to Black's awkward piece placement. The b7 pawn is weak, the knight on e8 weirdly placed and Ng5 is a constant threat for White. }
21. Nd5
{ We neutralize the knight on e8 and threaten Rxc6!. If we look carefully Black has hardly any moves and our compensation is tremendous. }
21... Bf8 22. Be3 Qxa2 23. g4
{ We will follow with Rbc5 against any threat from Black. The idea is that Ng5-h6-Nxf7-Kxf7-Bxh6 destroys Black's whole kingside. In addition, g4 allows us to prevent Bf5. A good exercise is to ask 'What can Black move? and discard each of their moves. }
