14... Nxd5
{ Otherwise, we will manage to play Bxb6 and the presence of double pawns would give us real chances of getting an advantage. }
15. exd5 Nc4 16. Bc5 Nd6
{ Black achieves the dreamed blockade but seems to me more playable than it really is. }
17. Nd2 f5 18. Qb3
{ We will bring our rooks to the c and d-files and later we can go for Nc4 or for Bxd6 followed by Nc4 ideas. We can also aim to occupy the c6-hole that black could leave attempting to develop the bishop on c8. In fact, in correspondence chess White has won a game from this position, so this is no mean feat.   We have to keep in mind that our bishop on g2 may be somewhat isolated from the game after Black's ...e5-e4, so we are not exempt from danger either, but I do think our play is much simpler. 1-0 @@StartBracket@@48@@EndBracket@@ Barkov,K @@StartBracket@@2434@@EndBracket@@-Mislin,R @@StartBracket@@2332@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2021 }
