7... Qb6 8. Nc3 Rd8 9. Na4 Qa6
{ After  9...Qxb3  10.axb3  Nbd7  11.Bf4  a 2700+ got here with Black only to realize that he can beraly move. 1-0  (57)  Ivanisevic,I  (2653)  -Ragger,M  (2698)  Berlin 2015   10...Na6  11.Bf4  I like this slow approach against Grunfeld players. We will play Rfc1 and bring the knight to c3, then expand with h3-g4 and the rook on a4 will nullify the knight on a6. It is a control position but, in practice, it has given very good results for White. }
10. cxd5 cxd5 11. Bf4
{ After e3 and Rfc1, Black will only realize how bad the queen is placed against moves like Bf1 or Nc5. }
