19... b5 20. axb6 axb6 21. Rxa8 Rxa8 22. e5
{ I like the fact that we have a rather intimidating plan such as g4-f5 and that Black can play freely, so maybe the position is annoting for the second player to deal with.   For example, the natural  22...Rc8  loses material after  23.Qa2!  threatening both Qxc4 and Bxc6. }
