18. d5 Nxe3 { Our next move comes as a shock for BLack: } 19. Nxf7 Rxf7 20.
Rxe3
{ The pawns dominate Black. I found a very colorful example of tactics that can work. White has the upper hand with normal moves, so there is no need to worry. }
20... exd5 21. c7 { Intending to continue with e6-Nxd5. } 21... Rxc7 22. Bxd5+
Kh8 23. Bxc4 { Black loses to the pin and the threat of Rxd7 followed by Rd8. }
