9. Rc1 Bd7
{ In case of  9...b5  10.Nd5  we will gain some presence on the c-file and the fact that the c7-pawn will be under permanent attack is very uncomfortable for the second player. They do not have a real counterplay, so we can focus oin capitalizing on that weakness. White's score is 70% in 100 games, so this shows that this position is not playable for Black.   Against  9...Bg4  we will continue with the typical  10.d5  move. }
10. Qd2 { We keep on improving the rest of our pieces. } 10... Re8
{ If  10...b5  we would again play  11.Nd5  . } 11. d5 { Now is the time! }
