7... Ne4 8. Nh4 { A common move that regains control of the e4-square. } 8...
Nxc3 9. bxc3 Bc8
{ We have allowed Black to weaken our structure in return for a couple of tempi, so now we have to play energetically. }
10. f4 c5
{ Against an attack on the flank it is best to counter in the center!   Avoiding f5 with  10...e6  would not be very effective since after  11.e4  we renew the idea.   After  10...f5  11.e4  I do not think the ...f5-break has improved Black's position at all. After e5 and Ba3 our position would be crushing. }
11. f5
{ The key idea. The strong point of this curious setup is that Black loses any flexibility of pawns on the kingside.   As we can see, they cannot move any pawn without losing material or being excessively weakened. In addition, Black will always have to deal with future sacrifices on g6 and have a weaker castled position having exchanged the knight on f6. }
