10. Qe2 { Reinforcing our c4-pawn and getting ready to go Rd1. } 10... exd4 11.
Nxd4 Nb6
{ 11...Re8  12.Rd1  Nb6  and Black is aiming for ...d6-d5  13.Qd3  defending the c4-pawn and we are ready now to push b2-b3. Black's plan has been disabled and should lose some tempi to regroup their pieces. }
12. Rd1 Qb4
{ This move will reveal an important detail that we have to remember by heart. }
13. Bf1 Na4 14. Nxa4 Qxa4 15. Qe1
{ With this subtlety we will leave Black's queen very badly placed. After f3-b3-Be3 we will have the ideal position and the black queen will be seriously out of play.   After  15.b3?!  black would benefit enormously from having exchanged two minor pieces after  15...Qa5  . }
