{ A direct consequence of not playing h3 is that it makes this knight jump possible. Black aims to go knight e5, provoking b3, jump the other knight into c5, and finally land a knight on d3. In this case, our normal development is sufficient as a response. }
11. h3 Nge5 12. b3 Nc5 13. Be3
{ The knight jump to d3 is harmless due to Re2. We will continue with Qc2-Rad1 with a great advantage. }
