16... Rc8 17. Bd3 a6 18. h4
{ By playing  18.Bf4  followed by e4, we will get a comfortable advantage, and we are aiming for expanding ourselves in the center and highlighting how misplaced the a5-knight is. With the move h4 my intention is to show some funnier positions. }
18... Rc5 19. h5 Rxd5 20. hxg6 hxg6 21. Rh4
{ Objectively, Black is fine, but the position is quite delicate to my eyes. Our opponent has to be careful not to lose in a few moves after we play something like Bh6 or Kg2-Rfh1. }
