21. Qc2
{ I love this move. Before including the moves h4 and ...h5 it was not possible, as Bg5 was impossible. Our idea is to play Qa2 followed by e4-Bf4. The key lies in controlling the c4 square and keeping Black busy solving the problem with the a5-knight. }
21... Rc7 22. Bg5 Qd7 23. Qa2 Rfc8 24. Rfc1
{ Black can barely move. We will continue with moves such as Kg2-f3-Be3 and we will see how it affects the fact that the knight on a5 is so far out of play. It is also important to keep in mind that Black has a very weak kingside and sacrifices like Bxg6 are on the menu. }
