e4
{ ...b4 is not possible because of the check on a4. Our idea is to play a very similar position to the mainline Benko with cxb5 and a4. We seem to have lost a tempo with a3, but we have also played e4 in one go, so we reach the same position. }
6... bxc4 7. Bxc4
{ We should go for the following setup: h3  (to limit the bishop on c8)  , Nf3 and O-O. After that we should continue with Re1, Bf4 and e5. Black's pieces are quite clumsy without the a6 square. }
