14... h5 15. Bg5
{ White's pressure on e7 limits Black's options. Here I quite like the plan to move Qc2 and Nd1-Ne3-Nc4. Note that the e8-knight is hopeless, and we have the queenside firmly under our control. Taking this into account, we can go for the e5-push in the center or even play on the queenside with Rb1 and b4. }
