{ If  5...Nc5  6.exd6  Bxd6  7.Nc3  we will continue Nf3 and Bg5 next and Black's compensation is little to nothing. }
6. e3 Bf5 7. Nc3
{ The matter lies in the pressure we exert on the pinned e4-knight. } 7... Ng3
8. e4 Nxe4 9. Bd3
{ White's active pieces are putting too much pressure on the weak black center. We will win a pawn and dominate the center. }
