{ We keep waiting for black to weaken the kingside with h6 or to move the knight to a6. In case of   9...Bf5  10.g4!  Bd7  and I love the idea of playing  11.a4!  to stop queenside counterplay and allow the rook to attack the kingside through a3!. }
