{ Very important intermediate move. In case of 10. exd5 we will need to face 0-0 and an eventual Re8+. This way we develop our bishop in one go. }
10... Bxa6 11. Bxa6 Nxa6 12. e5 { Important tematic move. } 12... Ng4 13. Nxd5
Nxe5
{ Including 13. ... 0-0 14. Bf4! Re8 would be painful after 15. 0-0 exchange everything on e5 and follow with f4! White is just winning, blacks castle is so weak to the following ideas f4-f5 + Qb3-Qc3 and Ra1-e1. }
14. Nxe5 Bxe5 15. Bh6 { Black is in trouble. } 15... Qh4 16. Qe3
{ In case of Qd4 taking and 0-0-0 would be great. Even something like f6 to play Kf7 runs into Nxf6! and f4. Black is stuck in the center for a while. }
