[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c5
{ This move is not as bad as it seems. Even Mamedyarov dared to play it on numerous occasions. }
3. cxd5 Nf6 4. e4
{ An interesting pawn sac which is based on keeping our strong pawn on d5 alive. }
4... Nxe4 5. dxc5 Nxc5 6. Nf3
{ Black has lost a lot of tempi with the knight and would wish to play ...g6 but, unfortunately, in this case this move would be met with Qd4. }
6... e6 7. Nc3 Be7 8. Bc4 O-O 9. O-O
{ The knight has no future on c5 and, after a move such as Qe2, the rooks will come and Black's position will be tremendously awkward and underdeveloped. }
