16. Nbd4
{ Our blockade on d4 is fantastic and Black will be left with a very passive bishop and a very exposed pawn structure. The plan of doubling our rooks on the c-file, followed by moving our pieces around with moves like Bh3 and Nd2, just waiting for the perfect moment to take on c4, seems very convincing. }
