{ Threatening Nxc6 and Nd6+. Black has only two playable options here. } 11...
Bd7 { This move offers a bit more resistance. } 12. Bf4 Rc8 13. Rc1
{ Black doesn't have useful moves, so we are in no hurry to play  13.Nd6+  . }
13... a6 14. Nd6+ Bxd6 15. Bxd6 Ne4 16. Ba3
{ Keeping our control of the diagonal. } 16... Qd2
{ Here we find a couple of recent games between titled players which followed with the critical continuation. }
17. Bxe6 fxe6 18. Qh5+ g6 19. Qh4
