9... c5 10. Qb3 Ra7
{ In view of this suboptimal development, it is quite strong to simply complete our development. }
11. Bb2 Be7 12. O-O O-O 13. Rfc1 Nbd7 14. Qd1
{ We will continue with moves such as Bf1 and Nc4 next, and Black will end up losing another tempo to relocate the rook. We see that we have given way to the rooks and minor pieces, and now the harmony of White's pieces is total.   The a-pawn will always be a problem for Black. I really like this line as an example of patience and focusing on improving the pieces. }
