{ 10...Nxd5  11.Nxd5  exd5  12.Bb2  and White has a considerable advantage since Black cannot move the f8 bishop and castle, which means that their position is very exposed. }
11. Ne4 exd5 12. Nxf6+ Qxf6 13. Rb1 Nc6 14. e4 Bg4 15. exd5 Bxf3 16. Re1+ Be7
17. Qxf3 Qxf3 18. gxf3 Nd4
{ Black will continue with Kd7 and the position is likely leading to a draw. ½-½ @@StartBracket@@30@@EndBracket@@ Esipenko,A @@StartBracket@@2654@@EndBracket@@-Van Foreest,J @@StartBracket@@2667@@EndBracket@@ Prague 2020 }
