h6
{ Preventing Bg5.   11...e5  12.Bg5  and Black's is practically lost, as after 13.Nd5+ the second player has to pay a high price for having the king stuck in the center. }
12. e5 Nd5 13. Nxd5+ exd5 14. Rd1 Nb6 15. Bd2
{ Our next move will be Rac1. We have completed our development and Black has a hardly playable IQP position. White is much better and the a3-f8 diagonal is still weak. }
