Nbd7 15. Nxd7 Bxd7 16. Ne5
{ Our next moves will likely be Rfd1 and Bf3.The bishop pair is a very comfortable mid-term advantage. Eventually we can also look for creating trouble on the a1-g7 diagonal.   The bishops on a7 and d7 are not ideal and I find it hard for Black to find the right path to follow, as their king is also stuck in the center. }
