10... Bd6 11. Bxd6 Qxd6 12. Ne5
{ The e5-knight is taboo due to 13. Nb5!. We are threatening Qb6!, squeezing Black's pieces. Please stop here for a moment to appreciate how we play in a way that we make the f5-bishop feel completely useless, as it only hits empty squares. }
12... Nd7 13. Nxd7 Qxd7 14. Na4
{ We will continue with Qb6 and O-O, after which Black's dark-squares will become completely weak, while our plan is to increase the pressure along the c-file. Another factor to bear in mind is to pay attention to imbalances on the kingside in order to take advantage of our total domination on the queenside. }
