13. Qc1 { Removing the queen from the X-ray of Black's d8-rook. } 13... Be6
{ An innocent move like Be7 or Bb4 would be met with Ne3! followed by Ncd5 taking advantage of the fact that Black's c-pawn is pinned. }
14. Ne4 Be7 15. Nxe5 Nxe5 16. Nc5 Bxc5 17. Qxc5
{ We will continue with b4 and Rfc1 with a clear advantage thanks to our bishop pair and the lack of flexibility of Black's kingside pawn structure. }
