{ Threatening a5-a6. If Black plays ...a6 we will play Ne4-Qc3, blocking Black's 3 queenside pawns with our 2 pawns and we will simply put our pieces on their best squares. After moves like O-O, Rfd1-Rac1-b4 and even h4, Black will have long-term issues. Because of this, Black usually goes for other move orders. }
