14. d5 exd5 15. exd5 O-O-O 16. Rd1
{ 16.dxc6!?  Qxd3  17.cxb7+  Kc7  and here both b4!? and Ne5!? give us an amazingly good position. We will usually play for a4 to activate our rook or completely dominate the light squares and reduce Black's bishop influence. The b7-pawn will not fall quickly, so the position will be very exciting to play from our point of view. }
16... Nb4 17. Qf1
{ Apart from the funny Bh3 we threaten to go a4. Black's castling is weak and, besides, knight jumps such as Ne5 will always be annoying. }
