{ 21...Bxg2+  22.Kxg2  and again we will continue with Qf3 and e4 followed by Be3 and Rah1. This version is much better due to the fact that our king is already on g2. }
22. Bxb7+ Kxb7 23. Qf3+ Nd5 24. e4 Qxf3+ 25. Nxf3
{ We will continue with moves such as Be3-Kg2-Rah1 and Black will struggle a lot to avoid a total collapse. }
