18... Qd1+ 19. Kh2 Bd6+ 20. Ne5 Bxg2 21. Kxg2 Bxe5
{ Taking with the pawn is tempting, but it leads to a very unpleasant position. }
22. dxe5 Qd5+ 23. f3 Qxe5 24. Bd2
{ Suddenly we realize how strong the bishop is against the knight and how weak h7 is. Black has no easy way to coordinate on both flanks at the same time and there is no comfortable square for the king. Taking this into account, our prospects are very promising. }
